description:
This is a 15 minute workout called 'Guided Breathing: Awaken Your Inner Monk-Mode (3 Rounds w/ timer)' from the channel Kitaro Waga.
The workout falls under Rest/Breathing exercises and Rest/Meditation.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Zen Flow and The Deep Recharge vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Never do hyperventilation-type breathwork in water or while driving.

The following will be a guided breathwork video where I integrate the Wim Hof Method breathing with the physiological sigh and mindfulness meditation. This video is a follow-up to my last video on the newly released study by Huberman's Lab.

A little bit about myself: I'm Kitaro, a Movement, Kung Fu, and breathwork practitioner and teacher. I try to publish weekly videos. So, if you like my vibe, please subscribe to this channel.
